		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><addressee>Mr Isaac Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName></p>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Curacao</placeName> <date>Novr 26<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1866</date>.</p>
				<p>Dear Sir.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I am possession of your of the <date><sic>3th</sic> August</date><lb/> ulto. contents of it duly noted&#44;  I return to you hereby the pro&#45;<lb/>spectus  list with the names of some friends on it as sub&#45;<lb/>scribers&#44; I am sorry I could not <sic>obtained</sic> some more up to<lb/> this&#44; but not to keep it longer by me I do so&#44; however I<lb/> will try always to get some of our people of <placeName>Nueva Gra&#45;<lb/>nada</placeName> &#38; of <placeName>Venezuela</placeName> when they come here&#44; I have not pre&#45;<lb/>sented to any of the reform people on acct the hate and<lb/> the <sic>deslike</sic> which they have for Judaism and being these <sic>reli&#45;<lb/>geous</sic> works I supposed they should have refused to sign it<lb/> their reform I assure you is not like of the others congregation&#44;<lb/> they revenge their capricious with religion matter by aboli&#45;<lb/>shing on every occasion the precepts of our Law&#44; as on the last<lb/> <date>Rosh a shana</date> no <hi rend="underline">sophar</hi> at all&#44; <date>Kipur day</date> <persName>Mr. Henriques<lb/> M. D.</persName> delivered a discourse in which saying to his people<lb/> that by fasting two hours that day it is quite sufficient and<lb/> his good <sic>advise</sic> made that nearly all the congregation have<lb/> done so&#44; among them selves many do not like such reform&#44;<lb/> but the chiefs ones <sic>geveeng</sic> always for <sic>reasen</sic> that the reform<lb/> of <placeName>New York</placeName> it is so&#44; as the Tefelim&#44; Tales<add>&#63;</add>&#44; Sophar&#44; Lulab<add>&#63;</add> riding<lb/> of the carriage and <sic>smocking</sic> on <date><sic>Saterday</sic></date>&#44; on cover in the<lb/> <sic>Sinagogue</sic>&#44; no celebration of <date>Purim</date> or <date><sic>Hannica</sic></date> no prayers at the<lb/> circumcision &#38; many <sic>others</sic> ceremonies which they have<lb/> <sic>aboleshed</sic></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><sic>intirly</sic> and calling that Progress&#44; I wish to know from<lb/> you if it is so or not in the Emannuel Temple of <placeName>New York</placeName><lb/> that I may in case if it is not to contradict them. They<lb/> are standing with same number of members as for last<lb/> 18 months. &#45; For the present I conclude with the hope to<lb/> write you soon again&#44; and remaining</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your Obdt Servt</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><persName role="author">B de Casseres</persName></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p><addressee>Isaac Leeser Esqr.</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><placeName>1227 Walnut Street</placeName>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(2)"><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
